               <msContents>
                  <summary change="#ai-catalogue">
                     <p>مرصاد العباد من المبدا الى المعاد.</p>
                     <p>A fine old copy of the Mirsada l-Ibád of Najmu'd-Din Dáya, who completed <lb/>it at Síwás in Asia Minor in Rajab 620/1223. See Rieu's Persian Catalogue, <lb/>pp. 38-39. In this MS. the author's name is given as follows (f. 231a):</p>
                     <p>ابو بكر بن عبد الله بن محمّد بن شاها وور الاسدي الرازي</p>
                     <p>This beautiful old MS. was transcribed in Cairo and finished on 10 Jumádà 11, <lb/>768/11 Feb., 1367, by Hájji Muhammad ibn Muhammad ibn Sa'd an-Nakhjuwání. <lb/>It contains 233 ff. of 25 x 18 c. and 17 ll.; large, clear naskh with rubrications. <lb/>This was one of 47 MSS. bought of the late Hájjí 'Abdu'l-Majid Belshah in <lb/>January, 1920.</p>
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="D_3-item1">
